\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 Well I stood up and - and said a - I saying - up from the meadows rich with corn, clear in the cold }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14229023\charrsid12668771 September}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771  morn, the 
clustered spires of Fredick Stand, green walled by the hills of Maryland. Round about the orchard creep, apple and peach tree from the deep. I stood up and I tried to put this into Shetland but I was stopped right away, I had to walk out on the floor and 
get the strap on each hand. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 When you went to school was the first time when you had to actually learn to stop using those words which you'd used in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 No, no, we were taught before we went to school. We didn't have to talk and we wouldn't have to speak in the Shetland dialect. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 I suppose some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14229023\charrsid12668771 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771  the children hadn't practiced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 Oh yes, some of them did but - of course they got away with it, it wasn't very long before they were told to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 Did your mother take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 Not much, except maybe at election time, when she might have been interested to know which party got in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 Did she ever have less food so that the rest of the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 There was generally always
 plenty to go round, but I can remember in the 1914-18 war when sugar was rationed she would have done without sugar in her tea so that we should get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 I can never remember us ever being told to touch the cap to anybody but ladies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 My sister 
when into the Dunrossness Sorting Office as an assistant when she left school in the 1920s, and for over 20 years has been Sub-Postmistress in the same office: as regards her jobs, I am afraid I can't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 My brother's occupation since he marrie
d in 1935, has been working on his croft and various jobs with the Shetland County Council, for the past year he has been caretaker at the new Dunrossness Primary School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 Fray Bentos.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 Ben Hur, by Lew Wallace - 'The copy that I first read was a prize my uncle got at school sometime in the 1890s.'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 The fisherman's shed was called a BOOTH.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7105026 RB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8352648\charrsid12668771 Barbara FREITCHIE.
\par }}